  <abstract displayLabel="Description">Byrd discusses his attendance at McKinley High School, including academics, sports, activities, influential teachers, older students, and graduates; his struggle to complete high school because of the need to drop out for work; the role of the community in raising children; disciplinary action he and other children received when they misbehaved; the lack of discipline and respect among young people today; and the need to rehabilitate nonviolent criminals.</abstract>
